Description: Fragment of flattened handle at neck join of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine brown-buff; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '220'. Name Ieron. Ieron I or II? Same die is used for an example from Samos.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (165)
